Preheat the oven to 220°C, bring a #saucepan{} of water to the boil. Heat a large #frying pan{} on medium high heat (no oil). Once hot, add the @Coconut & Chilli Marinated Chicken Breast{280%g}. Fry until browned, about ~{3%minutes} each side. Transfer to a #baking tray{} and roast until cooked through, ~{12-15%minutes}. Keep the pan!

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle!

Once the chicken is cooked, remove from the oven and pop on a #cutting board{} to rest.

Meanwhile, when boiling, add the @Jasmine Rice{150%g} to the water and cook until tender, ~{10-12%minutes}. Drain in a #sieve{}.

While everything cooks, slice your @Closed Cup Mushrooms{150%g}. Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{1}(grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Trim and finely slice the @Spring Onion{1}(finely sliced). Zest and halve the @Lime{1}.

Wash out your frying pan if there are any burnt bits. Pop the pan back on medium high heat with a drizzle of @oil{a drizzle}. Add the mushrooms, a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Stir fry until golden, ~{3-4%minutes}. Add the garlic, stir-fry for another ~{1%minute}.

Add the drained rice to the frying pan with the mushrooms. Add the @Ketjap Manis{25%g}, lime zest and a squeeze of lime juice. Stir fry until everything is piping hot. Taste and add salt, pepper and more lime juice if you want.

Spoon the rice into #bowls{}. Slice up the chicken and serve on top of the rice. Sprinkle over the spring onions. Chop the remaining lime into wedges and serve alongside. Enjoy!